        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 5:04PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 504 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gatlinburg, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gatlinburg, Harrisburg, Pittman Center, Pigeon Forge, Sevierville,
and Great Smoky Mountains National Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Morristown.</instruction>
